HEADWORD: Cablegram
<hw>Ca"ble*gram`</hw> <pr>(k⟦amac⟧"b'l*gr⟦acr⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cable</ets>, n. + Gr. <grk>gra`mma</grk> a writing, a
letter.]</ety> <def>A message sent by a submarine telegraphic
cable.</def> <note>[A recent hybrid, sometimes found in the
newspapers.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

